Sequence Information.Source: a 21-residue fragment from fish obtained via enzyme digestion and isolation

Literature Information.Literature: Discovery: a natural fragment isolated from enzyme digestion of fish.Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that this sequence is most similar (38.1%) toTemporin-MS1.Activity: Active against E. faecalis JCM 5803T (MIC 46 ug/ml), L. innocua ATCC 33090T (MIC 23 ug/ml), E. coli JM109 (MIC 46 ug/ml), B. coagulans CM 2257 (MIC 23 ug/ml), P. putida ATCC 12633 (MIC 23 ug/ml), S.enterica subsp. enterica NBRC 13245 (MIC 184 ug/ml), and P.vulgaris F24B (MIC > 184 ug/ml).
Literature Information.Author: Maky MA, Zendo T. 2021
Literature Information.Title: Generation and Characterization of Novel Bioactive Peptides from Fish and Beef Hydrolysates
